+Demof – Mini App Creation Plan (Ticket Exchange Platform)
+1. Project Overview
+
+Demof is a mini application that enables users to exchange, resell, or give away event tickets in a secure and easy way. The platform connects people who can no longer attend an event with those who are looking for tickets.
+
+2. Core Features
+2.1 User Accounts
+
+Email / phone / social login
+
+User profile with basic information
+
+Ticket ownership verification (optional)
+
+2.2 Ticket Listings
+
+Create a ticket listing (event name, date, seat, price, QR code upload)
+
+Edit or delete listings
+
+Mark ticket as sold / exchanged
+
+2.3 Ticket Exchange Mechanism
+
+Direct message between users
+
+Button: Request Exchange or Buy Ticket
+
+Automatic confirmation and ticket transfer system (optional MVP: manual confirmation)
+
+2.4 Event Search & Filtering
+
+Search by event name, city, category
+
+Filter by date, price, availability
+
+2.5 Notifications
+
+When a requested ticket becomes available
+
+Messages and exchange confirmations
+
+2.6 Security & Verification
+
+Basic verification of users
+
+Secure payment integration (Stripe/PayPal) – optional for MVP
+
+Fraud protection (warnings, reporting)
+
+3. Technology Stack
+Frontend
+
+React / React Native (for mobile mini-app)
+
+TailwindCSS or Material UI
+
+Backend
+
+Node.js + Express
+
+Database: MongoDB / PostgreSQL
+
+Authentication: JWT / OAuth
+
+Third-party Integrations
+
+Payment API: Stripe or PayPal
+
+Cloud storage for tickets: AWS S3 / Firebase Storage
+
+Notifications: Firebase Cloud Messaging
+
+4. Architecture Overview
+
+Client application communicates with REST API backend
+
+Database stores users, tickets, and transactions
+
+Storage service keeps uploaded ticket images
+
+Payment gateway handles financial operations (if included)
+
+5. Development Milestones
+Phase 1 — Planning & Design (1–2 weeks)
+
+Define MVP functionality
+
+Create wireframes & UI/UX design
+
+Prepare database schema
+
+Phase 2 — Backend Development (2–4 weeks)
+
+Set up authentication
+
+Implement ticket CRUD operations
+
+Implement messaging (basic)
+
+Add event search & filters
+
+Deploy backend
+
+Phase 3 — Frontend Development (3–6 weeks)
+
+Build UI components
+
+Integrate API endpoints
+
+Add ticket upload & preview
+
+Add messaging UI
+
+Implement notifications
+
+Phase 4 — Testing & QA (1–2 weeks)
+
+Unit and integration tests
+
+Usability testing
+
+Fix bugs and optimize performance
+
+Phase 5 — Launch & Iteration (ongoing)
+
+Publish the app (web or mobile)
+
+Collect user feedback
+
+Add advanced features: secure escrow payments, QR code auto-verification, analytics dashboard
+
+6. Optional Future Features
+
+AI-based fraud detection
+
+Dynamic price suggestions
+
+Event organizer partnerships
+
+Loyalty system or points for exchanges
+```
